  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "From the blood of Abel,.... \"Righteous Abel\", as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 23:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and so read the Arabic version here, and two manuscripts in the Bodleian library, and three of Stephens's copies; the Persic version renders it, \"innocent Abel\": he is mentioned because he was the first man that was slain, and he was slain because of his righteousness. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Unto the blood of Zacharias; in the Cambridge copy of Beza's, it is added, \"the son of Barachias\", as in Matthew 23:35 and so the Arabic version, \"the son of Barasciah\"; who he was; see Gill on Matthew 23:35. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Unto the blood of Zacharias; in the Cambridge copy of Beza's, it is added, \"the son of Barachias\", as in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 23:35",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and so the Arabic version, \"the son of Barasciah\"; who he was; see Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 23:35",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which perished between the altar and the temple; or \"the house\", that is, the holy place: and the Ethiopic version renders it, \"the holy house\"; here he died, being slain by the Jews; see the note, as before. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Verily I say unto you, it shall be required of this generation; as it was at the time of the destruction of Jerusalem. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Verily I say unto you, it shall be required of this generation; as it was at the time of the destruction of Jerusalem. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
